# Relay — Landing Page Prompt
## For: AI Coding Agents / Frontend Generators

---

## The Prompt

Build a minimal, high-polish landing page for a product called **Relay**.

---

### Product

Relay is a shared memory layer for AI-assisted dev teams. When you use Claude Code, Copilot, Codex, or Cursor — your AI only knows what YOU know. Relay makes every AI on your team share one brain. Decisions, conventions, architecture choices, bugs fixed — stored once, known by everyone's AI instantly. Bring your own tool, bring your own credits. Relay just connects the brains.

---

### Visual Direction

**Strict constraints:**
- Background: pure black `#000000` only. No gradients on the background, no dark greys, no navy. Black.
- Primary text: white `#ffffff`
- Accent: single white with varying opacity for hierarchy. No color accents at all — no blue, no purple, no green. Pure monochrome.
- The ONE exception: a very subtle `#ffffff08` or `#ffffff05` for card/surface backgrounds — barely visible, just enough to separate panels from the void.

**Typography:**
- Display / hero headline: `Space Grotesk` — bold, wide, slightly geometric. Not Inter, not Geist, not the default.
- Body / UI text: `Inter` at 400/450 weight
- Code / memory entries / monospace moments: `JetBrains Mono`
- All labels and eyebrows: uppercase, `0.12em` letter spacing, `opacity: 0.4`, small (11-12px)

**Aesthetic:**
- Brutally minimal. Every element must justify its existence.
- No illustrations. No icons unless functional.
- No rounded hero cards with gradients. No glowing orbs. No particle effects.
- The only animation allowed: a single typewriter/stream effect in the hero showing memory entries appearing one by one. Everything else is static or subtle fade-in on scroll.
- Whitespace is aggressive. Sections breathe.
- Feels like: Linear's website met a zine. Spare, confident, slightly cold.

